# Phase 10.6 â€” LangGraph Workflow & Parallel Specialist Execution

This rule applies only to Phase 10.6: adding/completing a real LangGraph workflow in the coordinator-agent and executing specialist nodes in parallel where practical.

## Scope

Implement the coordinator daily-report workflow as a real LangGraph graph with these logical nodes:

* `fetch_context`
* `run_sales`
* `run_content`
* `run_support`
* `merge`
* `submit`

The graph must preserve all previous Phase 10 behavior:

* Step 10.1 star topology
* Step 10.2 per-node timeouts
* Step 10.3 AgentOutput persistence
* Step 10.4 mock integration behavior
* Step 10.5 real coordinator endpoint and Celery completion wiring

## Required behavior

1. Add or complete a real LangGraph workflow in `coordinator-agent`.
2. Use the existing coordinator state model or a compatible typed state.
3. Represent the planned workflow nodes as LangGraph nodes or clearly documented equivalents.
4. Execute `run_sales`, `run_content`, and `run_support` in parallel where practical.
5. Preserve coordinator-only orchestration:

   * coordinator calls sales/content/support
   * sales/content/support do not call each other
6. Preserve per-node timeout boundaries from Step 10.2.
7. Preserve AgentOutput persistence from Step 10.3.
8. Preserve final report submission behavior from Step 10.5.
9. Preserve partial-failure behavior:

   * specialist failures/timeouts become structured warnings where appropriate
   * successful specialist outputs still flow into merge/submit
10. Keep the public coordinator endpoint contract stable unless a minimal compatibility change is required.
11. Do not auto-approve or execute actions.
12. Do not introduce direct DB access from agents.
13. Do not hardcode Prestia-specific business logic.

## Non-goals

* No Step 10.7 DB-backed final E2E closure in this step.
* No frontend/dashboard work.
* No Phase 12 Prestia demo polish.
* No real LLM calls.
* No real Instagram publishing/sending.
* No external side effects.
* No agent-to-agent mesh.
* No broad rewrite of specialist agents.
* No raw PII, prompts, JWTs, Authorization headers, or full payload logging.

## Testing requirements

Add deterministic tests for:

* LangGraph graph creation/compilation
* graph contains or represents `fetch_context`, `run_sales`, `run_content`, `run_support`, `merge`, `submit`
* specialist fan-out/fan-in or parallel execution behavior
* timeout behavior still applies under graph execution
* AgentOutput persistence still works under graph execution
* partial specialist failure still produces `warnings[]`
* star topology remains enforced
* Step 10.5 endpoint can run the graph-backed workflow
* no real LLM API keys or live external services required

Existing Phase 10 tests from 10.1â€“10.5 must remain passing or be minimally updated to the new graph-backed workflow contract.

